-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Tue Jun 10, 2014 09:59AM EDT
-- None



June 10 (Reuters) -  The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1330 GMT on Tuesday:

** Time Warner Inc <TWX.N> is in talks to buy a major stake in Vice Media, valuing the media company at about $2.2 billion, Sky News reported, citing sources. [ID:nL4N0OQ4H9]  ** The sale by billionaire investor Wilbur Ross of his entire shareholding in Bank of Ireland <BKIR.I> was priced at 0.265 euros per share, Deutsche Bank, the placing's bookrunner, said in a statement. [ID:nL5N0OR1KJ]  ** U.S. private equity firm Fortress Investment Group LLC <FIG.N> ended its 10-year foray into German real estate on Tuesday, selling a $1 billion stake in Gagfah <GFJG.DE>, one of Germany's largest property firms. [ID:nL5N0OR32W]  ** Botox maker Allergan Inc <AGN.N> rejected a sweetened $53 billion takeover offer from Valeant Pharmaceuticals International <VRX.TO> and activist investor William Ackman, reiterating that it undervalues the company and is too risky for shareholders. [ID:nL2N0OR0HZ]  ** B/E Aerospace Inc <BEAV.O>, an aircraft seat maker and parts distributor, will split into two publicly traded companies, making it easier for the company to pursue a sale of its businesses. [ID:nL4N0OR2PO]  ** The government of Pakistan will sell its 19.8 percent stake in lender United Bank Ltd <UBL.KA> for up to 42 billion Pakistani rupees ($426.27 million) on Wednesday, IFR magazine reported on Tuesday. [ID:nL4N0OR1XS]  ** PPL Corp <PPL.N> and Riverstone Holdings LLC said on Monday they would combine their merchant power generation businesses into a new standalone, publicly traded independent power producer. [ID:nL4N0OR175]  ** Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena <BMPS.MI> said on Tuesday it had sold 500 million euros ($680.75 million) of bad loans to U.S. private equity firm Fortress Investment Group <FIG.N>, the latest in a raft of disposals of sour loans by Italian banks. [ID:nL5N0OR0ZG]  ** International Game Technology <IGT.N>, the Las Vegas-based slot machine maker, has hired Morgan Stanley <MS.N> to explore a sale as the gaming industry pursues consolidation to combat slow growth, people familiar with the matter said on Monday. [ID:nL2N0OQ1JC]  ** The Philippine government will start auctioning off two waterworks infrastructure contracts this month worth an estimated 43 billion pesos ($988 million) under its public-private partnership program, a senior official said. [ID:nL4N0OR1N9]  ** Biotech group arGEN-X, which develops new drugs to treat cancer and autoimmune diseases, said on Tuesday it was planning an IPO to be listed on the Brussels stock exchange. [ID:nL5N0OR0WE]  ** ON Semiconductor Corp <ONNN.O>, a maker of power-management chips, said it would buy Aptina Imaging for about $400 million in cash to accelerate its growth in the automotive and industrial markets. [ID:nL4N0OQ45U]